    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="916"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d916">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/11–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative in Korea</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-18">November 18,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. Cite <gloss target="#t_Zpol1">Zpol</gloss> 13320. Pass <gloss
                        target="#t_Gadel1">GADel</gloss>, Paris.<note n="1" xml:id="d916fn1">This
                        was done November 19.</note> Understand following message sent today via
                    commercial radio to UNGA Chairman Evatt: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“On behalf of the members of the Korean National Assembly, I take
                            pleasure in presenting to you the following resolution passed by the
                            Assembly at its 106th session on November 17, 1948. ‘Whereas the
                            National Assembly and Government of the Republic of Korea were legally
                            established through the general elections of May 10, 1948 in accordance
                            with the resolution of the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> General
                            Assembly of November 14, 1947 and that of its interim committee of
                            February 26, 1948 and by the whole will of our Korean people, be it
                            resolved unanimously that the members of the Korean National Assembly
                            express their desire to request that the <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                                >UN</gloss> General Assembly will approve the Government of the
                            Republic of Korea as the legal government of Korea, further resolved
                            that we express our heartfelt appreciation for your untiring efforts for
                            world peace.’ Shin Ik Hi, Chairman Korean National Assembly.”<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d916fn2">Telegram 244, December 2, from Seoul, reported a
                                briefer resolution unanimously passed by the Korean National
                                Assembly for the General Assembly at Paris (501.BB
                                Korea/12–248).</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
